RACE.FOOTNOTES: MYSTIFICATION gained command outside a rival early, cleared and crossed over on the first turn, met the bid from outer rival leaving the backstretch, maintained command through the far turn, shook free in upper stretch and inched away. PRECISION STRIKE tracked the pace from inside, moved into range in the middle stages, moved out in upper stretch and outkicked CARIBBEAN KING for second. CARIBBEAN KING raced up close on the inside then tipped out into the backstretch, challenged the leader at the seven-sixteenths pole, kept the pressure on through the far turn, could not kick on with the winner in upper stretch and got edged for the place honors. ST IGNACIO pulled and steadied off heels early, tugged on the inside, put to right-handed urging in the lane and kept on to round out the superfecta. MEGA MOON forwardly placed two wide into the first turn, bumped outer rival and checked around the bend, chased two wide into the lane and needed to find more late. QUALITY WINS was keen early stalked off the rail, got bumped three wide on the clubhouse turn, stalked three deep into the second bend, lost ground while continued three wide to the stretch and failed to rally. HULA CANDY broke a bit slow and got bumped from inside before being sandwiched between rivals and clipped feet or bobbled early, traveled three then four deep around the far turn and improved position. DEFENSOR FORTIS tossed his head, shifted out and bumped rival at the start, chased wide through the first turn, bid four then three deep on the second bend but flattened out in the lane. ARROMAX broke a step slow on the outside, unhurried in the early going and moved into the two path, raced near the inside then two wide on the far turn, lugged inward in upper stretch and failed to menace. BRING HIM HOME got bumped from outside and had to check early then became rank prior to the first turn, trailed early then went outside a rival, moved in on the backstretch, ridden along through the far turn, cut the corner into the lane and failed to make an impact. HEARTBREAK KID traveled in mid-pack outside a rival, came three wide into the lane and failed to menace. BIG ATTITUDE came in and bumped rival early, trailed into and around the far turn and had little left for the stretch run.
